{title: Heart Healer}
{artist: Mel Tillis}
{composer: Written by Thomas Gmeiner and John Greenebaum}

[G]Well I fell to sweet temptation
A victim to the devils vow
And [D7]most of my dreams got lost in the bargain
I [C]could use a little comfort [G]now
When I get love life’s inspiration
It just knocks me flat on my face
[D7]You came along to pick me up
And [C]I’m looking for more than a [D7]taste
I [G]need a sweetheart healer like you
It’s [D7]been a long time over [G]due
I looked around and around and around and around
For a [D7]sweetheart healer like [G]you
Now my friends and close relations
Say I ought to take it slow
But [D7]I can’t subdue what I’m feeling for you
And [C]it’s time to let it [G]show
There’s no need for moderation
Now I think it’s plain to see
[D7]I got the desire to unlock the chains
And [C]I’m handing you the [D7]key
Repeat #3 x2